═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
1. SAFE-HARBOR — ALWAYS FREE, FOR EVERYONE, REGARDLESS OF SIZE
═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════

The following uses are granted free of charge to every user with no
revenue or size restriction whatsoever:

  (a) Evaluation and trials
  (b) Development and prototyping
  (c) Automated testing and continuous integration
  (d) Benchmarking and performance measurement
  (e) Academic and non-commercial research
  (f) Personal, hobby, and homelab use
  (g) Non-production staging environments

If your use fits one of these categories, it is free — even for the
largest company in the world.  No license key, no registration, no
obligation.

═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
2. PRODUCTION USE — TWO-GATE TRIGGER
═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════

A commercial license is required ONLY when BOTH of the following are
true at the same time:

  Gate A — PRODUCTION USE.
    The use is production or mission-critical, meaning any use that
    is NOT on the safe-harbor list in Section 1.  This includes:
    • In-house operations the organization depends on
    • Consumer-facing or customer-facing deployment

  Gate B — ENTITY SIZE.
    The entity's total annual gross revenue, aggregated across the
    entity and all its affiliates (entities under common control by
    ownership of more than 50% of voting equity), is USD $3,000,000
    or more for the most recently completed fiscal year.

If EITHER gate is not met, the use is free.  If BOTH gates are met,
a commercial license must be obtained.

OUTCOMES:

| Entity Revenue | Use              | Result                        |
|----------------|------------------|-------------------------------|
| Under $3M      | Production       | FREE                          |
| $3M or more    | Safe-harbor      | FREE                          |
| Under $3M      | Safe-harbor      | FREE                          |
| $3M or more    | Production       | COMMERCIAL LICENSE REQUIRED   |

═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
3. COMMERCIAL LICENSE
═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════

A Standard Commercial License is available for entities meeting both
gates.  Contact emerging.systems for terms, pricing, and volume
options.

═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
4. GRACE PERIOD
═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════

An entity that crosses the $3M revenue threshold while already
running in production has a ninety (90) day grace period from the
date it exceeds the threshold to obtain a commercial license.
During the grace period, continued use is permitted without
penalty.

═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
5. WHAT THIS LICENSE IS NOT
═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════

This is a source-available ("fair-source") license.  It is NOT an
OSI-approved open-source license.  It discriminates by user and
field of use (the two gates), which the Open Source Definition does
not permit.  Describe it as "source-available" or "fair-source" —
never as "open source."

